			<description><![CDATA[ <p><img src="http://cache.gawker.com/assets/images/gawker/2008/12/AAfakereal4.jpg" width="250" height="274" align="left" hspace="4" vspace="2">All subversive things in our culture must eventually be co-opted by the very things that they subvert. It's the American way. The <a class="autolink" rel="nofollow" title="Click here to read more posts tagged AMERICAN APPAREL" href="http://gawker.com/tag/american-apparel/">American Apparel</a> ad spoofer&mdash;who had <a href="http://gawker.com/search/american+apparel+ad+spoofer/bydate/?timerange=all">a months-long run of fame</a> for creating super-porny ripoffs of AA ad posters (which eventually turned out <a href="http://gawker.com/5047338/the-american-apparel-ad-spoofers-final-joke-on-us-all">to be Photoshop fakes</a> by the people at <a href="http://www.stereohell.com/door/">Stereohell</a>)&mdash;has now become the subject of an actual <a href="http://animalnewyork.com/news/2008/12/fake-aa-ad-artist-now-real-aa.php">American Apparel ad</a>. In <em>Vice</em> magazine, naturally! Click through for photos of <a class="autolink" rel="nofollow" title="Click here to read more posts tagged DOV CHARNEY" href="http://gawker.com/tag/dov-charney/">Dov Charney</a>'s victory over artistic mockery:</p> <p><img src="http://cache.gawker.com/assets/images/gawker/2008/12/AAfakereal.jpg" width="600" height="800" style="display:block;" /><br> <img src="http://cache.gawker.com/assets/images/gawker/2008/12/AAfakereal2.jpeg" width="600" height="309" style="display:block;" /></p> <p>[<a href="http://www.stereohell.com/door/?p=1180">Stereohell</a> via <a href="http://animalnewyork.com/news/2008/12/fake-aa-ad-artist-now-real-aa.php">Copyranter at Animal</a>]</p> ]]></description>
